articles.description: A.J. Mosby had 22 points on 9-of-11 shooting, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range, and Dante Sterling scored 15 points to help Alcorn State beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 84-52 on Monday night.
articles.headline: Mosby scores 22, Alcorn State hits 12 3s in win over UAPB

articles.description: Baylor head coach Scott Drew breaks down the importance of his team's victory and how hard his players fought in the Bears' 74-73 double overtime victory over Texas.
articles.headline: Drew 'proud' of his team

images.caption: Baylor head coach Scott Drew breaks down the importance of his team's victory and how hard his players fought in the Bears' 74-73 double overtime victory over Texas.
images.name: Drew 'proud' of his team

articles.description: Tiwian Kendley scored 24 points and Morgan State held Florida A&M to 18 first-half points on its way to a 74-48 win on Monday night.
articles.headline: Morgan State dominates Florida A&M 74-48

articles.description: The No. 20 Mountaineers shoot over 50 percent from the field and 3-point range with four players scoring in double digits en route to an 82-66 win against the Horned Frogs.
articles.headline: West Virginia runs by TCU

images.caption: The No. 20 Mountaineers shoot over 50 percent from the field and 3-point range with four players scoring in double digits en route to an 82-66 win against the Horned Frogs.
images.name: West Virginia runs by TCU

articles.description: Manu Lecomte misses his shot but Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. capitalizes on the miss with a putback dunk to go ahead of Texas in the final seconds of double overtime.
articles.headline: Baylor's Lual-Acuil Jr. delivers dagger putback dunk

articles.description: Ivy Smith Jr. had 22 points and seven rebounds on Monday night to help Grambling beat Texas Southern 78-55 for its 10th straight win.
articles.headline: Grambling wins 10th straight, beats Texas Southern 78-55
